  "prompt": "How do I treat a crooked smile?",
  "response": "Treating a crooked smile depends on the underlying cause. Here are some potential approaches:\n\n1. Medical causes:\n- Bell's Palsy: May resolve on its own or require medication/physical therapy\n- Stroke: Requires immediate medical attention and rehabilitation\n- Facial nerve damage: May need surgical intervention\n\n2. Dental/orthodontic solutions:\n- Braces or clear aligners to correct teeth alignment\n- Dental implants or veneers\n- Jaw alignment treatments\n\n3. Cosmetic treatments:\n- Botox to balance facial muscles\n- Facial exercises\n- Symmetry-enhancing makeup techniques\n\n4. Surgical options:\n- Reconstructive surgery\n- Nerve repair\n- Muscle repositioning\n\n5. Non-surgical approaches:\n- Physical therapy\n- Facial muscle exercises\n- Massage therapy\n\nRecommended steps:\n1. Consult a healthcare professional to diagnose the specific cause\n2. Get a comprehensive medical evaluation\n3. Follow professional recommendations for treatment\n4. Consider multiple treatment options\n\nAlways seek professional medical advice to determine the most appropriate treatment for your specific situation.",
